translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah was sitting at Xan's former desk, studying a series of papers she had strew out across the tables."
    new "Sarah was sitting at Xan's former desk, studying a series of papers she had strew out across the tables."

    old "It had been more than a few days since Sarah had rested in the bathhouse, and even longer since she had come across Xan's writings."
    new "It had been more than a few days since Sarah had rested in the bathhouse, and even longer since she had come across Xan's writings."

    old "And then there was the book."
    new "And then there was the book."

    old "The book Razaphel claimed was the foundation of the order of mages that Xan had belonged to, but of which Sarah knew frighteningly little."
    new "The book Razaphel claimed was the foundation of the order of mages that Xan had belonged to, but of which Sarah knew frighteningly little."

    old "If she had listened to him and gone to the citadel, she no doubt would know more."
    new "If she had listened to him and gone to the citadel, she no doubt would know more."

    old "But then again, Sarah realized, she would not have had her freedom."
    new "But then again, Sarah realized, she would not have had her freedom."

    old "She'd rather be ignorant and free, she knew that much."
    new "She'd rather be ignorant and free, she knew that much."

    old "Flipping one of the pages from a document near the edge of the desk, Sarah nearly wondered why she even bothered."
    new "Flipping one of the pages from a document near the edge of the desk, Sarah nearly wondered why she even bothered."

    old "Not only did she not understand, worse than that, she barely even knew where to begin."
    new "Not only did she not understand, worse than that, she barely even knew where to begin."

    old "In front of her, she saw the air darken and a form take shape."
    new "In front of her, she saw the air darken and a form take shape."

    old "Old friend..."
    new "Old friend..."

    old "The spirit's voice had something playful about it."
    new "The spirit's voice had something playful about it."

    old "Come to deliver more riddles? Or perhaps taunt me today?"
    new "Come to deliver more riddles? Or perhaps taunt me today?"

    old "Razaphel's form splintered near the edges like mist forming on the surface of ice."
    new "Razaphel's form splintered near the edges like mist forming on the surface of ice."

    old "Rather the opposite."
    new "Rather the opposite."

    old "Answers, should you be in need of any."
    new "Answers, should you be in need of any."

    old "Sarah suddenly leaned forward."
    new "Sarah suddenly leaned forward."

    old "Answers?"
    new "Answers?"

    old "That is, supposing you are still interested in learning more of the book."
    new "That is, supposing you are still interested in learning more of the book."

    old "Sarah almost shouted the words."
    new "Sarah almost shouted the words."

    old "I have considered the easiest way for you to make sense of the matter."
    new "I have considered the easiest way for you to make sense of the matter."

    old "It paused, before continueing."
    new "It paused, before continueing."

    old "You will need to consult a book titled 'A Brief Investigation on Ethics'."
    new "You will need to consult a book titled 'A Brief Investigation on Ethics'."

    old "You want me to read more books?"
    new "You want me to read more books?"

    old "I told you that you would need a base of knowledge to even begin to understand the book you seek to grapple with."
    new "I told you that you would need a base of knowledge to even begin to understand the book you seek to grapple with."

    old "Or have you perhaps decided to begin your investigation yourself."
    new "Or have you perhaps decided to begin your investigation yourself."

    old "Sarah knew that she had."
    new "Sarah knew that she had."

    old "Ignoring the spirit's advice, she had opened the book from Xan's private study and tried reading it herself."
    new "Ignoring the spirit's advice, she had opened the book from Xan's private study and tried reading it herself."

    old "More than merely complex, it also leaned heavily on the usage of unknown words and words in odd and very particular definitions."
    new "More than merely complex, it also leaned heavily on the usage of unknown words and words in odd and very particular definitions."

    old "Less than three pages in and Sarah understood that she simply did not possess the knowledge to read it."
    new "Less than three pages in and Sarah understood that she simply did not possess the knowledge to read it."

    old "I'm willing to consider your approach."
    new "I'm willing to consider your approach."

    old "But where can I find a copy of the book you mentioned?"
    new "But where can I find a copy of the book you mentioned?"

    old "Well, it is quite a rare print. One could perhaps be found in the vault of Bagrad, but I suppose that is less of an option these days."
    new "Well, it is quite a rare print. One could perhaps be found in the vault of Bagrad, but I suppose that is less of an option these days."

    old "The spirit's words lingered in the air."
    new "The spirit's words lingered in the air."

    old "Then again, there is a perfectly functional library in this house."
    new "Then again, there is a perfectly functional library in this house."

    old "In here? I don't remember a book by that name."
    new "In here? I don't remember a book by that name."

    old "No, not this library. Nor his private study. You need to visit the central library."
    new "No, not this library. Nor his private study. You need to visit the central library."

    old "The central library?"
    new "The central library?"

    old "Yes. I suspect Xan kept you from that room as well, but it is quite easy to find should you be willing enough to find it."
    new "Yes. I suspect Xan kept you from that room as well, but it is quite easy to find should you be willing enough to find it."

    old "Sarah stood up from behind the desk."
    new "Sarah stood up from behind the desk."

    old "Where would that be, exactly?"
    new "Where would that be, exactly?"

    old "Leave this room, turn down the hall, second door on your left."
    new "Leave this room, turn down the hall, second door on your left."

    old "Sarah eyed the spirit for any signs of deceit."
    new "Sarah eyed the spirit for any signs of deceit."

    old "That's a storage room."
    new "That's a storage room."

    old "It is whatever the master of the house wills it to be. What do you will it to be?"
    new "It is whatever the master of the house wills it to be. What do you will it to be?"

    old "Sarah paused before answering."
    new "Sarah paused before answering."

    old "The central library..."
    new "The central library..."

    old "Then I suspect you will find it waiting for you."
    new "Then I suspect you will find it waiting for you."

    old "Go ahead and explore it. I suspect you'll find it most useful."
    new "Go ahead and explore it. I suspect you'll find it most useful."

    old "Sarah knew she had few other options other than to do what the spirit wanted."
    new "Sarah knew she had few other options other than to do what the spirit wanted."

    old "Suddenly, Sarah heard the softest of footsteps, entering the room."
    new "Suddenly, Sarah heard the softest of footsteps, entering the room."

    old "I hope I'm not bothering you."
    new "I hope I'm not bothering you."

    old "Never. I'm glad you're here. This place gets awfully lonely without you."
    new "Never. I'm glad you're here. This place gets awfully lonely without you."

    old "And it's lonely for me as well when you're not around."
    new "And it's lonely for me as well when you're not around."

    old "Do you mind if I sit here with you? I know you wanted to study today, but I just feel a bit restless, and I don't want to be alone."
    new "Do you mind if I sit here with you? I know you wanted to study today, but I just feel a bit restless, and I don't want to be alone."

    old "Of course, but we won't be sitting here."
    new "Of course, but we won't be sitting here."

    old "Sarah set out towards the direction that Razaphel had given her."
    new "Sarah set out towards the direction that Razaphel had given her."

    old "Walking through the hallway, Sarah traced the hallway."
    new "Walking through the hallway, Sarah traced the hallway."

    old "Eventually she reached the door that Razaphel had instructed her to seek out."
    new "Eventually she reached the door that Razaphel had instructed her to seek out."

    old "For a moment, Sarah observed the door."
    new "For a moment, Sarah observed the door."

    old "She knew this door. Had used it on occasion and she knew what was behind it. Little more than a storage room."
    new "She knew this door. Had used it on occasion and she knew what was behind it. Little more than a storage room."

    old "But by now, Sarah had come to understand that little about the house made sense."
    new "But by now, Sarah had come to understand that little about the house made sense."

    old "She placed her hand on the handle, pushed the door open, and stepped through."
    new "She placed her hand on the handle, pushed the door open, and stepped through."

    old "Sarah had come across many unnatural things since she had begun her studies under Xan."
    new "Sarah had come across many unnatural things since she had begun her studies under Xan."

    old "Witnessing so many things that staggered the mind, over time, Sarah felt herself grow numb to them."
    new "Witnessing so many things that staggered the mind, over time, Sarah felt herself grow numb to them."

    old "And yet in this moment, Sarah felt the rush of awe that she imagined she had lost."
    new "And yet in this moment, Sarah felt the rush of awe that she imagined she had lost."

    old "Her eyes roamed the vast space, impossibly large, unable to fit within the house and yet untroubled by such restraints of physics."
    new "Her eyes roamed the vast space, impossibly large, unable to fit within the house and yet untroubled by such restraints of physics."

    old "Seemingly infinite rows of bookcases, containing an equally infinite number of books, reaching out in every direction."
    new "Seemingly infinite rows of bookcases, containing an equally infinite number of books, reaching out in every direction."

    old "Sarah could hear her footsteps echo through the enormous hall as she walked further inside."
    new "Sarah could hear her footsteps echo through the enormous hall as she walked further inside."

    old "She heard Samayra walking close to her, equally struck silent by the majesty of the place."
    new "She heard Samayra walking close to her, equally struck silent by the majesty of the place."

    old "Sarah searched for words she could not find."
    new "Sarah searched for words she could not find."

    old "Walking past one of the bookcases, Sarah allowed her eyes to linger across all the different tomes."
    new "Walking past one of the bookcases, Sarah allowed her eyes to linger across all the different tomes."

    old "She read the titles softly to herself, as if to commit them to memory."
    new "She read the titles softly to herself, as if to commit them to memory."

    old "The library in Rosanna had been impressive, but this room made the library of her childhood seem like a joke."
    new "The library in Rosanna had been impressive, but this room made the library of her childhood seem like a joke."

    old "How could one name anything else a library if they had seen this place."
    new "How could one name anything else a library if they had seen this place."

    old "I can't believe it..."
    new "I can't believe it..."

    old "Sarah heard her own voice echo through the hall, running away further and further from her, hinting at all the spaces she had not yet discovered."
    new "Sarah heard her own voice echo through the hall, running away further and further from her, hinting at all the spaces she had not yet discovered."

    old "This is even bigger than the library in Bagrad!"
    new "This is even bigger than the library in Bagrad!"

    old "Sarah could hear Samayra was as stunned as her."
    new "Sarah could hear Samayra was as stunned as her."

    old "She smiled at Samayra."
    new "She smiled at Samayra."

    old "I was actually thinking the same thing just now."
    new "I was actually thinking the same thing just now."

    old "Walking further, ever deeper into the vast library, Sarah finally came upon a clearing."
    new "Walking further, ever deeper into the vast library, Sarah finally came upon a clearing."

    old "An open space, emerging from between the many book cases."
    new "An open space, emerging from between the many book cases."

    old "Positioned in the center was a long wooden table with some chairs carved out of heavy oak wood."
    new "Positioned in the center was a long wooden table with some chairs carved out of heavy oak wood."

    old "Sarah walked up closer."
    new "Sarah walked up closer."

    old "Samayra was close behind her. The girl seemed desperate not to get seperated from Sarah."
    new "Samayra was close behind her. The girl seemed desperate not to get seperated from Sarah."

    old "Suddenly, a voice came to her."
    new "Suddenly, a voice came to her."

    old "Voice\" \"What do you seek?"
    new "Voice\" \"What do you seek?"

    old "Sarah found herself surprised at how little the voice scared her, despite it seemingly appearing from nowhere at all."
    new "Sarah found herself surprised at how little the voice scared her, despite it seemingly appearing from nowhere at all."

    old "The soft, melodic rhythm of the voice made it impossible to suspect even a hint of danger."
    new "The soft, melodic rhythm of the voice made it impossible to suspect even a hint of danger."

    old "Voice\" \"I am the curator of this place."
    new "Voice\" \"I am the curator of this place."

    old "But where are you?"
    new "But where are you?"

    old "Curator\" \"I occupy no particular space."
    new "Curator\" \"I occupy no particular space."

    old "Curator\" \"My function is to assist the master in maintaining the existing collection."
    new "Curator\" \"My function is to assist the master in maintaining the existing collection."

    old "The master? Do you mean Xan?"
    new "The master? Do you mean Xan?"

    old "Curator\" \"Xanthippe was the master of this space, but the connection was recently severed."
    new "Curator\" \"Xanthippe was the master of this space, but the connection was recently severed."

    old "Curator\" \"For lack of alternative, you would appear to be the current master."
    new "Curator\" \"For lack of alternative, you would appear to be the current master."

    old "Sarah felt a rush run through her body."
    new "Sarah felt a rush run through her body."

    old "She began to realize she had inherited far more than just her freedom when she betrayed Xan."
    new "She began to realize she had inherited far more than just her freedom when she betrayed Xan."

    old "What...what can you do, exactly?"
    new "What...what can you do, exactly?"

    old "Curator\" \"I maintain a full and complete index of all existing volumes in the collection."
    new "Curator\" \"I maintain a full and complete index of all existing volumes in the collection."

    old "Curator\" \"Should you be in need of finding any, I will assist you in locating them."
    new "Curator\" \"Should you be in need of finding any, I will assist you in locating them."

    old "Sarah nodded as the voice explained."
    new "Sarah nodded as the voice explained."

    old "On some level, despite how odd it all seemed, it made a degree of sense to her."
    new "On some level, despite how odd it all seemed, it made a degree of sense to her."

    old "A library like this would take an army to maintain. Of course mages would find more efficient ways if magic allowed it."
    new "A library like this would take an army to maintain. Of course mages would find more efficient ways if magic allowed it."

    old "Sarah suddenly felt frightened by just how little she really knew of the magical world, now that she could no longer rely on Xan."
    new "Sarah suddenly felt frightened by just how little she really knew of the magical world, now that she could no longer rely on Xan."

    old "She raised up her head and spoke loudly."
    new "She raised up her head and spoke loudly."

    old "Do you have a copy of 'The Hollow World?'"
    new "Do you have a copy of 'The Hollow World?'"

    old "Curator\" \"A copy of such a book does not exist within the current inventory."
    new "Curator\" \"A copy of such a book does not exist within the current inventory."

    old "Curator\" \"Existing models classify that book as exceptionally rare."
    new "Curator\" \"Existing models classify that book as exceptionally rare."

    old "She already had a copy of it, but it still surprised her that the entire library itself wouldn't have a single copy."
    new "She already had a copy of it, but it still surprised her that the entire library itself wouldn't have a single copy."

    old "Still, she had not come here to procure a secondary version."
    new "Still, she had not come here to procure a secondary version."

    old "Do you have a copy of 'A Brief Investigation on Ethics?'"
    new "Do you have a copy of 'A Brief Investigation on Ethics?'"

    old "Sarah spoke even more forcefully this time."
    new "Sarah spoke even more forcefully this time."

    old "For a moment, the voice was absent, then it rushed back into her head."
    new "For a moment, the voice was absent, then it rushed back into her head."

    old "Curator\" \"The current library contains seventeen copies of A Brief Investigation on Ethics. Seven original prints, five second editions and five third editions."
    new "Curator\" \"The current library contains seventeen copies of A Brief Investigation on Ethics. Seven original prints, five second editions and five third editions."

    old "Curator\" \"A Brief Investigation on Ethics was first written by the philosopher Lu-Fan, hailing from the current region known to you as the Far East."
    new "Curator\" \"A Brief Investigation on Ethics was first written by the philosopher Lu-Fan, hailing from the current region known to you as the Far East."

    old "Curator\" \"First drafted twelve-hundred years ago, the first translated copies made their way into the Union Kingdoms some two centuries later."
    new "Curator\" \"First drafted twelve-hundred years ago, the first translated copies made their way into the Union Kingdoms some two centuries later."

    old "Curator\" \"It was not until another century later, when the book reached the early Mythran empire, when it rose to prominence."
    new "Curator\" \"It was not until another century later, when the book reached the early Mythran empire, when it rose to prominence."

    old "Curator\" \"Ever since, the book has been primarily used as introductory reading for students at the Mythran universities."
    new "Curator\" \"Ever since, the book has been primarily used as introductory reading for students at the Mythran universities."

    old "The voice paused."
    new "The voice paused."

    old "Curator\" \"Is this the book you seek?"
    new "Curator\" \"Is this the book you seek?"

    old "Yes...I think."
    new "Yes...I think."

    old "Curator\" \"Which copy would you prefer?"
    new "Curator\" \"Which copy would you prefer?"

    old "The...most recent one?"
    new "The...most recent one?"

    old "Curator\" \"Very well, please take a seat. I shall deliver you a third edition copy of the requested item momentarily."
    new "Curator\" \"Very well, please take a seat. I shall deliver you a third edition copy of the requested item momentarily."

    old "Sarah did as the voice instructed, sitting down at the wooden table."
    new "Sarah did as the voice instructed, sitting down at the wooden table."

    old "All around her, she could hear the buzzing and whirling of the library, as though it was alive."
    new "All around her, she could hear the buzzing and whirling of the library, as though it was alive."

    old "Perhaps it was, she thought, what did she really know if it."
    new "Perhaps it was, she thought, what did she really know if it."

    old "Opposite of her, Sarah could see Samayara strolling past some of the bookcases."
    new "Opposite of her, Sarah could see Samayara strolling past some of the bookcases."

    old "I'm sorry that I have some work to do."
    new "I'm sorry that I have some work to do."

    old "Do you think you'll be alright?"
    new "Do you think you'll be alright?"

    old "Samayra nodded, never taking her eyes of the books."
    new "Samayra nodded, never taking her eyes of the books."

    old "I was looking for a copy of 'The Desert Blooms'..."
    new "I was looking for a copy of 'The Desert Blooms'..."

    old "Suddenly, the voice rushed in again."
    new "Suddenly, the voice rushed in again."

    old "Curator\" \"'The Desert Blooms'. We have Thirty-eight copies within the current inventory."
    new "Curator\" \"'The Desert Blooms'. We have Thirty-eight copies within the current inventory."

    old "Curator\" \"Would you like me to procure one?"
    new "Curator\" \"Would you like me to procure one?"

    old "Yes, please...uhm...spirit?"
    new "Yes, please...uhm...spirit?"

    old "Curator\" \"I am not a spirit."
    new "Curator\" \"I am not a spirit."

    old "Flying through the air, a copy of the book Samayra had requested flew towards her, pausing only just before striking her."
    new "Flying through the air, a copy of the book Samayra had requested flew towards her, pausing only just before striking her."

    old "The novel floated softly in the air until Samayra grabbed it."
    new "The novel floated softly in the air until Samayra grabbed it."

    old "As always, genuine excitement came easy to the girl."
    new "As always, genuine excitement came easy to the girl."

    old "Samayra made her way towards the table."
    new "Samayra made her way towards the table."

    old "Have you ever read it?"
    new "Have you ever read it?"

    old "Sarah shook her head. She hadn't even heard of it before."
    new "Sarah shook her head. She hadn't even heard of it before."

    old "Really? In Bagrad everyone has read it...even the servants."
    new "Really? In Bagrad everyone has read it...even the servants."

    old "Those that could read, of course."
    new "Those that could read, of course."

    old "Samayra was quick to add."
    new "Samayra was quick to add."

    old "But even those that can't read have heard the stories from it."
    new "But even those that can't read have heard the stories from it."

    old "Sarah smiled as she saw how happy Samayra appeared."
    new "Sarah smiled as she saw how happy Samayra appeared."

    old "It's a story of this girl, and she's awesome! Her brother goes missing in the desert and so she has to go find him."
    new "It's a story of this girl, and she's awesome! Her brother goes missing in the desert and so she has to go find him."

    old "Then, as she goes looking for him, she has all these adventures, it's really fun."
    new "Then, as she goes looking for him, she has all these adventures, it's really fun."

    old "Samayra's entire body language grew increasingly excited with each word."
    new "Samayra's entire body language grew increasingly excited with each word."

    old "You should really read it."
    new "You should really read it."

    old "Sure, I'm sure you can bring a copy of it back to the house. I'll promise I'll read it."
    new "Sure, I'm sure you can bring a copy of it back to the house. I'll promise I'll read it."

    old "Samayra smiled, happy that someone could see her in a place like this."
    new "Samayra smiled, happy that someone could see her in a place like this."

    old "Suddenly, a book came flying out from one of the corridors."
    new "Suddenly, a book came flying out from one of the corridors."

    old "Rushing through the air, it went straight for Sarah's head."
    new "Rushing through the air, it went straight for Sarah's head."

    old "Only to stop and freeze, inches away from her body. The book floated in the air."
    new "Only to stop and freeze, inches away from her body. The book floated in the air."

    old "Surely there are better ways of bringing me a book than hurling it at my face?"
    new "Surely there are better ways of bringing me a book than hurling it at my face?"

    old "Sarah reached out and grabbed the book from the air."
    new "Sarah reached out and grabbed the book from the air."

    old "Curator\" \"There are no more efficient means than the means utilized in this space."
    new "Curator\" \"There are no more efficient means than the means utilized in this space."

    old "Sarah rolled her eyes. There was efficient, and then there was whatever this was."
    new "Sarah rolled her eyes. There was efficient, and then there was whatever this was."

    old "Holding the book in her hand, Sarah read the cover."
    new "Holding the book in her hand, Sarah read the cover."

    old "It weighed heavy, thick leather, expensive."
    new "It weighed heavy, thick leather, expensive."

    old "To her surprise, it wasn't all that long, perhaps even a little short of the average book she read."
    new "To her surprise, it wasn't all that long, perhaps even a little short of the average book she read."

    old "Sarah placed the book down on the table and flipped open the cover."
    new "Sarah placed the book down on the table and flipped open the cover."

    old "Sarah looked up from the book, distracted."
    new "Sarah looked up from the book, distracted."

    old "If you're just going to be sitting here reading...do you mind if I go explore?"
    new "If you're just going to be sitting here reading...do you mind if I go explore?"

    old "Of course not. Just promise me you won't do anything dangerous."
    new "Of course not. Just promise me you won't do anything dangerous."

    old "Of course not. And even if there is danger, I'll just scream and you can come save me."
    new "Of course not. And even if there is danger, I'll just scream and you can come save me."

    old "The girl smiled before turning and running away."
    new "The girl smiled before turning and running away."

    old "Her footsteps echoed, slowly growing softer as she got further and further away."
    new "Her footsteps echoed, slowly growing softer as she got further and further away."

    old "Before long, Sarah found herself all alone in the clearing."
    new "Before long, Sarah found herself all alone in the clearing."

    old "Leaning across the table, Sarah brought her eyes close to the first page of the book."
    new "Leaning across the table, Sarah brought her eyes close to the first page of the book."

    old "Small scratches ran across the surface of the page, hinting at its age. Despite that, the book was well maintained."
    new "Small scratches ran across the surface of the page, hinting at its age. Despite that, the book was well maintained."

    old "Sarah eyed the list of chapters."
    new "Sarah eyed the list of chapters."

    old "History. Ethics. The names of a few famous philosophers."
    new "History. Ethics. The names of a few famous philosophers."

    old "In the moment, Sarah made up her mind."
    new "In the moment, Sarah made up her mind."

    old "She wanted to know more about the order of mages that Xan had belonged to, if only to know how she could keep herself safe."
    new "She wanted to know more about the order of mages that Xan had belonged to, if only to know how she could keep herself safe."

    old "To achieve that, she'd need to study. To learn enough so she could learn more still."
    new "To achieve that, she'd need to study. To learn enough so she could learn more still."

    old "And the only way that she know how to do that was by following the guide of Razaphel, who seemed to know more than she did."
    new "And the only way that she know how to do that was by following the guide of Razaphel, who seemed to know more than she did."

    old "Leaning forward, Sarah began to read."
    new "Leaning forward, Sarah began to read."

    old "Around her, she could slowly feel the other distractions from the library fade."
    new "Around her, she could slowly feel the other distractions from the library fade."

    old "Before long, the small sounds and noises had faded."
    new "Before long, the small sounds and noises had faded."

    old "Piece by piece, the whole of the library seemed to dissapear until it was only her and the book."
    new "Piece by piece, the whole of the library seemed to dissapear until it was only her and the book."

    old "Growing up in Rosanna, Sarah had mostly grown up reading books on history, the kind that allowed her to distinguish between the dozens of noble houses."
    new "Growing up in Rosanna, Sarah had mostly grown up reading books on history, the kind that allowed her to distinguish between the dozens of noble houses."

    old "That knowledge had lost its use when her homeland fell, and most houses she could name were now either snuffed out or living as refugees."
    new "That knowledge had lost its use when her homeland fell, and most houses she could name were now either snuffed out or living as refugees."

    old "Other subjects, such as warfare, were generally not considered required reading for noble women."
    new "Other subjects, such as warfare, were generally not considered required reading for noble women."

    old "The only reason Sarah had read as much books on strategy was because she had tried to help Thomas."
    new "The only reason Sarah had read as much books on strategy was because she had tried to help Thomas."

    old "That use also no longer mattered."
    new "That use also no longer mattered."

    old "But philosophy, of what little she had known of it, had always been the realm of the advisors and librarians."
    new "But philosophy, of what little she had known of it, had always been the realm of the advisors and librarians."

    old "Those who gathered knowledge for the sake of it."
    new "Those who gathered knowledge for the sake of it."

    old "And yet, Sarah now found herself enthralled by the book before her, exploring the topic in a way that proved both accessible and expansive."
    new "And yet, Sarah now found herself enthralled by the book before her, exploring the topic in a way that proved both accessible and expansive."

    old "There was not much depth to any of the particulars it touched on, but rather, it formed the context by which she could begin to understand the field."
    new "There was not much depth to any of the particulars it touched on, but rather, it formed the context by which she could begin to understand the field."

